Class PopupAdapter

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.MenuElement
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JCellPopup

    public class PopupAdapter
extends javax.swing.JPopupMenu
    A subclass of the JPopupMenu class intended to be used as an aid in defining the starting and finishing points of a path with the JCellMouseListener within the pathfinding visualization GUI. Therefore this popup menu will contain only two items: "Set cell as start" and "Set cell as finish". This is an adapter implementation in the sense that this class only defines the layout of the popup menu; the functionalities are to be implemented by an extension of this class.
    See Also:
    JCellMouseListener, JPopupMenu, Serialized Form
